title: Obama stands firm against lifting U.S. oil export ban despite potential economic benefits
text: By threatening to veto a bill greenlighting oil exports, President Obama last week sent a powerful message to Congress and to the American public: The administration is unlikely to sign off on any measures expanding fossil fuel production and sales, even if those measures carry economic benefits for the U.S. ... ...
